The Presidential Election Petitions Tribunal has refused an application by the Hope Democratic Party (HDP) to bring additional witnesses in its petition against the election of President Muhammadu Buhari. The five-member panel of justices presided by Justice Mohammed Garba on Tuesday ruled that the application constitutes a substantial alteration as provided in the Electoral Act, 2010 Paragraphs 14(1) and (2) of the First Schedule. Justice Garba said having brought the application outside the 21 days of filing the petition on May 15, 2019, it cannot be granted. He however granted the first prayer of the party requesting to correct clerical errors in the letters contained in t Presidential Tribunal: C4C, Ojinika withdraw petition against Buhari Election tribunal in a week Buhari seeks to dismiss Atikuâ€™s petition as tribunal begins hearing Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin